rComments: He sucks as a teacher, really nothing else to say.
Listens to you play for 30 minutes. Tells you to "make music" or "count property" and then makes you play again for 25 more minutes. Been like that for the whole year. He should consider retirement.
Amateur teacher, boring performer, never listens to students, predictably bureaucratic. Disappointing prof.
This graduate level course was phenomenal! It was well organized, very interesting, and had a reasonable work load for a graduate level course. The professor demonstrates excellent teaching!

quite a good solid performer of course, but as a person and teacher not very good.  He needs to know, as do other instructors, that playing an instrument and teaching require different mannerisms....the diva attitude must be non-existent when teaching....

Although somewhat aloof in person, he is the 1st choice for a piano prof. since Jean Desmarias was "discontinued". Marking is fair are accredited, but don't expect special attention: He will not risk his reputation by endorsing an underdog student & has limited repertorial tastes. Has good pedagogy.
Could be a nice man if he were to ever learn basic manners. Talent should not equal boorish and rude behaviour.

arrogant, unclear, sloppy teacher, and very poor people skills. he's all about himself and his stupid french piano music.  I would rather give the pope a daily bath than have another piano lesson with him! his partner's cool though!
